article.headline: N. Iowa 81, Drake 59
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa -- Johnny Moran scored 20 points and Northern Iowa trounced Drake 81-59 Saturday to take over sole possession of first place in the Missouri Valley Conference. Kwadzo (ka-JOH) Ahelegbe added 16 points for the Panthers, who won their sixth straight and snapped a four-game losing streak against the Bulldogs. It was perhaps the best performance yet for the surging Panthers (12-6, 6-1). They raced ahead 46-19 late in the first half, then started the second half with an 18-3 run to take their largest lead, 65-28. Northern Iowa shot 51.7 percent from the floor and had 17 assists against just four turnovers. Josh Parker scored a season-high 25 points to lead Drake (13-6, 4-3), which had won 10 straight over Division I opponents from Iowa. Bulldogs star Josh Young was held to just 3 points. Bradley will pull even with the Panthers atop the Valley if it beats Southern Illinois Sunday.
